  <a href="#0" id="0">
   We present a sentiment analysis-based approach to online dispute detection.
  </a>
  <a href="#1" id="1">
   We create a large-scale dispute corpus from Wikipedia Talk pages to study the problem.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   A sentiment prediction model based on isotonic CRFs is proposed to output sentiment labels at the sentence-level.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   Experiments on our dispute corpus also demonstrate that classifiers trained with sentiment tagging features outperform others that do not.
  </a>
